and in Wales the chronicler  Geoffrey  of Monmouth (  d. 1155 ). The original form and meaning of the name is disputed. According to one theory, it is merely a variant of   Godfrey ;  others derive the first part from the Germanic word <i>gawia</i> ‘territory’, <i>walah</i> ‘stranger’, or <i>gisil</i> ‘pledge’. Medieval forms can be found to support all these theories, and it is possible that several names have fallen together, or that the name was subjected to reanalysis by folk etymology at an early date."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Geoffrey Trussel I was born in 1340, in England, United Kingdom. He had at least 1 son with Mrs. Geoffrey Trussel I. He died about 1390, at the age of 51."},"et":{"1340–about 1390":"1340–umbes 1390","1342–Female":"1342–Surnud","1362–1412":"1362–1412","1340–1390":"1340–1390","about 1390":"umbes 1390","1412":"1412","1342":"1342","1340":"1340","1362":"1362","1390":"1390","Aston, Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Aston, Staffordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England, United Kingdom":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1340–about 1390":"1340–noin 1390","1342–Female":"1342–Kuollut","1362–1412":"1362–1412","1340–1390":"1340–1390","about 1390":"noin 1390","1412":"1412","1342":"1342","1340":"1340","1362":"1362","1390":"1390","Aston, Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Aston, Staffordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England, United Kingdom":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1340–about 1390":"1340–environ 1390","1342–Female":"1342–Décédée","1362–1412":"1362–1412","1340–1390":"1340–1390","about 1390":"environ 1390","1412":"1412","1342":"1342","1340":"1340","1362":"1362","1390":"1390","Aston, Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Aston, Staffordshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","England, United Kingdom":"Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Geoffrey Trussel I est né en 1340, à Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Il a eu au moins 1 fils avec Mrs. Geoffrey Trussel I. Il est décédé environ 1390, à l’âge de 51 ans